name: DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT
desc: Passed to clear to clear the current depth buffer.

name: STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT
desc: Passed to clear to clear the current stencil buffer.

name: COLOR_BUFFER_BIT
desc: Passed to clear to clear the current color buffer.

name: POINTS
desc: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw single points.

name: LINES
desc: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw lines. Each vertex connects to the one after it.

name: LINE_LOOP
desc: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw lines. Each set of two vertices is treated as a separate line segment.

name: LINE_STRIP
desc: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw a connected group of line segments from the first vertex to the last.

name: TRIANGLES
desc: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw triangles. Each set of three vertices creates a separate triangle.

name: TRIANGLE_STRIP
desc: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw a connected group of triangles.

name: TRIANGLE_FAN
desc: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw a connected group of triangles. Each vertex connects to the previous and the first vertex in the fan.

name: ZERO
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to turn off a component.

name: ONE
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to turn on a component.

name: SRC_COLOR
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the source elements color.

name: ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by one minus the source elements color.

name: SRC_ALPHA
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the source's alpha.

name: ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by one minus the source's alpha.

name: DST_ALPHA
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the destination's alpha.

name: ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by one minus the destination's alpha.

name: DST_COLOR
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the destination's color.

name: ONE_MINUS_DST_COLOR
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by one minus the destination's color.

name: SRC_ALPHA_SATURATE
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the minimum of source's alpha or one minus the destination's alpha.

name: CONSTANT_COLOR
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to specify a constant color blend function.

name: ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_COLOR
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to specify one minus a constant color blend function.

name: CONSTANT_ALPHA
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to specify a constant alpha blend function.

name: ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_ALPHA
desc: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to specify one minus a constant alpha blend function.

name: FUNC_ADD
desc: Passed to blendEquation or blendEquationSeparate to set an addition blend function.

name: FUNC_SUBTRACT
desc: Passed to blendEquation or blendEquationSeparate to specify a subtraction blend function (source - destination).

name: FUNC_REVERSE_SUBTRACT
desc: Passed to blendEquation or blendEquationSeparate to specify a reverse subtraction blend function (destination - source).

name: BLEND_EQUATION
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current RGB blend function.

name: BLEND_EQUATION_RGB
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current RGB blend function. Same as BLEND_EQUATION

name: BLEND_EQUATION_ALPHA
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current alpha blend function. Same as BLEND_EQUATION

name: BLEND_DST_RGB
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current destination RGB blend function.

name: BLEND_SRC_RGB
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current destination RGB blend function.

name: BLEND_DST_ALPHA
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current destination alpha blend function.

name: BLEND_SRC_ALPHA
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current source alpha blend function.

name: BLEND_COLOR
desc: Passed to getParameter to return a the current blend color.

name: ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the array buffer binding.

name: ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current element array buffer.

name: LINE_WIDTH
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current lineWidth (set by the lineWidth method).

name: ALIASED_POINT_SIZE_RANGE
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current size of a point drawn with gl.POINTS

name: ALIASED_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the range of available widths for a line. Returns a length-2 array with the lo value at 0, and hight at 1.

name: CULL_FACE_MODE
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current value of cullFace. Should return FRONT, BACK, or FRONT_AND_BACK

name: FRONT_FACE
desc: Passed to getParameter to determine the current value of frontFace. Should return CW or CCW.

name: DEPTH_RANGE
desc: Passed to getParameter to return a length-2 array of floats giving the current depth range.

name: DEPTH_WRITEMASK
desc: Passed to getParameter to determine if the depth write mask is enabled.

name: DEPTH_CLEAR_VALUE
desc: Passed to getParameter to determine the current depth clear value.

name: DEPTH_FUNC
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current depth function. Returns NEVER, ALWAYS, LESS, EQUAL, LEQUAL, GREATER, GEQUAL, or NOTEQUAL.

name: STENCIL_CLEAR_VALUE
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the value the stencil will be cleared to.

name: STENCIL_FUNC
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current stencil function. Returns NEVER, ALWAYS, LESS, EQUAL, LEQUAL, GREATER, GEQUAL, or NOTEQUAL.

name: STENCIL_FAIL
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current stencil fail function. Should return KEEP, REPLACE, INCR, DECR, INVERT, INCR_WRAP, or DECR_WRAP.

name: STENCIL_PASS_DEPTH_FAIL
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current stencil fail function should the depth buffer test fail. Should return KEEP, REPLACE, INCR, DECR, INVERT, INCR_WRAP, or DECR_WRAP.

name: STENCIL_PASS_DEPTH_PASS
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the current stencil fail function should the depth buffer test pass. Should return KEEP, REPLACE, INCR, DECR, INVERT, INCR_WRAP, or DECR_WRAP.

name: STENCIL_REF
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the reference value used for stencil tests.

name: VIEWPORT
desc: Returns an Int32Array with four elements for the current viewport dimensions.

name: SCISSOR_BOX
desc: Returns an Int32Array with four elements for the current scissor box dimensions.

name: STATIC_DRAW
desc: Passed to bufferData as a hint about whether the contents of the buffer are likely to be used often and not change often.

name: STREAM_DRAW
desc: Passed to bufferData as a hint about whether the contents of the buffer are likely to not be used often.

name: DYNAMIC_DRAW
desc: Passed to bufferData as a hint about whether the contents of the buffer are likely to be used often and change often.

name: ARRAY_BUFFER
desc: Passed to bindBuffer or bufferData to specify the type of buffer being used.

name: ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER
desc: Passed to bindBuffer or bufferData to specify the type of buffer being used.

name: BUFFER_SIZE
desc: Passed to getBufferParameter to get a buffer's size.

name: BUFFER_USAGE
desc: Passed to getBufferParameter to get the hint for the buffer passed in when it was created.

name: CURRENT_VERTEX_ATTRIB
desc: Passed to getVertexAttrib to read back the current vertex attribute.

name: CULL_FACE
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off culling. Can also be used with getParameter to find the current culling method.

name: FRONT
desc: Passed to cullFace to specify that only front faces should be culled.

name: BACK
desc: Passed to cullFace to specify that only back faces should be culled.

name: FRONT_AND_BACK
desc: Passed to cullFace to specify that front and back faces should be culled.

name: BLEND
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off blending. Can also be used with getParameter to find the current blending method.

name: DEPTH_TEST
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the depth test. Can also be used with getParameter to query the depth test.

name: DITHER
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off dithering. Can also be used with getParameter to find the current dithering method.

name: POLYGON_OFFSET_FILL
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the polygon offset. Useful for rendering hidden-line images, decals, and or solids with highlighted edges. Can also be used with getParameter to query the scissor test.

name: SAMPLE_ALPHA_TO_COVERAGE
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the alpha to coverage. Used in multi-sampling alpha channels.

name: SAMPLE_COVERAGE
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the sample coverage. Used in multi-sampling.

name: SCISSOR_TEST
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the scissor test. Can also be used with getParameter to query the scissor test.

name: STENCIL_TEST
desc: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the stencil test. Can also be used with getParameter to query the stencil test.

name: NO_ERROR
desc: Returned from getError.

name: INVALID_ENUM
desc: Returned from getError.

name: INVALID_VALUE
desc: Returned from getError.

name: INVALID_OPERATION
desc: Returned from getError.

name: OUT_OF_MEMORY
desc: Returned from getError.

name: CONTEXT_LOST_WEBGL
desc: Returned from getError.

name: CW
desc: Passed to frontFace to specify the front face of a polygon is drawn in the clockwise direction

name: CCW
desc: Passed to frontFace to specify the front face of a polygon is drawn in the counter clockwise direction

name: DONT_CARE
desc: There is no preference for this behavior.

name: FASTEST
desc: The most efficient behavior should be used.

name: NICEST
desc: The most correct or the highest quality option should be used.

name: GENERATE_MIPMAP_HINT
desc: Hint for the quality of filtering when generating mipmap images with WebGLRenderingContext.generateMipmap().

name: FRAGMENT_SHADER
desc: Passed to createShader to define a fragment shader.

name: VERTEX_SHADER
desc: Passed to createShader to define a vertex shader

name: COMPILE_STATUS
desc: Passed to getShaderParamter to get the status of the compilation. Returns false if the shader was not compiled. You can then query getShaderInfoLog to find the exact error

name: DELETE_STATUS
desc: Passed to getShaderParamter to determine if a shader was deleted via deleteShader. Returns true if it was, false otherwise.

name: LINK_STATUS
desc: Passed to getProgramParameter after calling linkProgram to determine if a program was linked correctly. Returns false if there were errors. Use getProgramInfoLog to find the exact error.

name: VALIDATE_STATUS
desc: Passed to getProgramParameter after calling validateProgram to determine if it is valid. Returns false if errors were found.

name: ATTACHED_SHADERS
desc: Passed to getProgramParameter after calling attachShader to determine if the shader was attached correctly. Returns false if errors occurred.

name: ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTES
desc: Passed to getProgramParameter to get the number of attributes active in a program.

name: ACTIVE_UNIFORMS
desc: Passed to getProgramParamter to get the number of uniforms active in a program.

name: MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS
desc: The maximum number of entries possible in the vertex attribute list.

name: MAX_TEXTURE_IMAGE_UNITS
desc: Implementation dependent number of maximum texture units. At least 8.

name: NEVER
desc: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will never pass. i.e. Nothing will be drawn.

name: LESS
desc: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is less than the stored value.

name: EQUAL
desc: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is equals to the stored value.

name: LEQUAL
desc: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is less than or equal to the stored value.

name: GREATER
desc: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is greater than the stored value.

name: NOTEQUAL
desc: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is not equal to the stored value.

name: GEQUAL
desc: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is greater than or equal to the stored value.

name: ALWAYS
desc: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will always pass. i.e. Pixels will be drawn in the order they are drawn.

name: TEXTURE0 - 31
desc: A texture unit.

name: ACTIVE_TEXTURE
desc: The current active texture unit.

name: VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_DIVISOR_ANGLE
desc: Describes the frequency divisor used for instanced rendering.

name: UNMASKED_VENDOR_WEBGL
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the vendor string of the graphics driver.

name: UNMASKED_RENDERER_WEBGL
desc: Passed to getParameter to get the renderer string of the graphics driver.

name: MAX_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT
desc: Returns the maximum available anisotropy.

name: TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT
desc: Passed to texParameter to set the desired maximum anisotropy for a texture.

name: COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT
desc: A DXT1-compressed image in an RGB image format.

name: COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT
desc: A DXT1-compressed image in an RGB image format with a simple on/off alpha value.

name: COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT
desc: A DXT3-compressed image in an RGBA image format. Compared to a 32-bit RGBA texture, it offers 4:1 compression.

name: COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT
desc: A DXT5-compressed image in an RGBA image format. It also provides a 4:1 compression, but differs to the DXT3 compression in how the alpha compression is done.

name: COMPRESSED_R11_EAC
desc: One-channel (red) unsigned format compression.

name: COMPRESSED_SIGNED_R11_EAC
desc: One-channel (red) signed format compression.

name: COMPRESSED_RG11_EAC
desc: Two-channel (red and green) unsigned format compression.

name: COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RG11_EAC
desc: Two-channel (red and green) signed format compression.

name: COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2
desc: Compresses RBG8 data with no alpha channel.

name: COMPRESSED_RGBA8_ETC2_EAC
desc: Compresses RGBA8 data. The RGB part is encoded the same as RGB_ETC2, but the alpha part is encoded separately.

name: COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ETC2
desc: Compresses sRBG8 data with no alpha channel.

name: COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ETC2_EAC
desc: Compresses sRGBA8 data. The sRGB part is encoded the same as SRGB_ETC2, but the alpha part is encoded separately.

name: COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2
desc: Similar to RGB8_ETC, but with ability to punch through the alpha channel, which means to make it completely opaque or transparent.

name: COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2
desc: Similar to SRGB8_ETC, but with ability to punch through the alpha channel, which means to make it completely opaque or transparent.

name: COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG
desc: RGB compression in 4-bit mode. One block for each 4×4 pixels.

name: COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG
desc: RGBA compression in 4-bit mode. One block for each 4×4 pixels.

name: COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG
desc: RGB compression in 2-bit mode. One block for each 8×4 pixels.

name: COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG
desc: RGBA compression in 2-bit mode. One block for each 8×4 pixe

name: COMPRESSED_RGB_ETC1_WEBGL
desc: Compresses 24-bit RGB data with no alpha channel.

name: COMPRESSED_RGB_ATC_WEBGL
desc: Compresses RGB textures with no alpha channel.

name: COMPRESSED_RGBA_ATC_EXPLICIT_ALPHA_WEBGL
desc: Compresses RGBA textures using explicit alpha encoding (useful when alpha transitions are sharp).

name: COMPRESSED_RGBA_ATC_INTERPOLATED_ALPHA_WEBGL
desc: Compresses RGBA textures using interpolated alpha encoding (useful when alpha transitions are gradient).

name: UNSIGNED_INT_24_8_WEBGL
desc: Unsigned integer type for 24-bit depth texture data.

name: HALF_FLOAT_OES
desc: Half floating-point type (16-bit).

name: RGBA32F_EXT
desc: RGBA 32-bit floating-point color-renderable format.

name: RGB32F_EXT
desc: RGB 32-bit floating-point color-renderable format.

name: MIN_EXT
desc: Produces the minimum color components of the source and destination colors.

name: MAX_EXT
desc: Produces the maximum color components of the source and destination colors.

name: SRGB_EXT
desc: Unsized sRGB format that leaves the precision up to the driver.

name: SRGB_ALPHA_EXT
desc: Unsized sRGB format with unsized alpha component.

name: SRGB8_ALPHA8_EXT
desc: Sized (8-bit) sRGB and alpha formats.

name: FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COLOR_ENCODING_EXT
desc: Returns the framebuffer color encoding.

name: FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT_OES
desc: Indicates the accuracy of the derivative calculation for the GLSL built-in functions: dFdx, dFdy, and fwidth.

desc: Framebuffer color attachment point

desc: Maximum number of framebuffer color attachment points

name: MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS_WEBGL
desc: Maximum number of draw buffers

name: VERTEX_ARRAY_BINDING_OES
desc: The bound vertex array object (VAO).

name: QUERY_COUNTER_BITS_EXT
desc: The number of bits used to hold the query result for the given target.

name: CURRENT_QUERY_EXT
desc: The currently active query.

name: QUERY_RESULT_EXT
desc: The query result.

name: QUERY_RESULT_AVAILABLE_EXT
desc: A Boolean indicating whether or not a query result is available.

name: TIME_ELAPSED_EXT
desc: Elapsed time (in nanoseconds).

name: TIMESTAMP_EXT
desc: The current time.

name: GPU_DISJOINT_EXT
desc: A Boolean indicating whether or not the GPU performed any disjoint operation.
